```

# New framework
any new services should go in ServerScriptService.Server.Services
any new server modules should go in ServerScriptService.Server.Modules

any new client controllers should go in ReplicatedStorage.Client.Controllers
any new client modules should go in ReplicatedStorage.Client.Modules

to require a service or controller, just require it like you would a normal module.

there also exists playerAdded , playerRemoving , and characterAdded functions you can use directly on the services. these will be called after init

for networking always use Net, don't make any new remotes
if you need a new package, drop it in ReplicatedStorage.Packages

all modules are required on startup, then init is called synchronously. don't do an infinite loop or preferably yield at all without task.spawning it inside init, there's a warning if you do just in case. dont yield outside of it either, there should usually never be a need.

index the players data and PlayerGui using ClientGlobals.PlayerData and ClientGlobals.PlayerGui respectively

# Replicator
for player data on the client, we're using a custom module that handles the replication completely automatically. index it through ClientGlobals.PlayerData
No manual replication when a replication system exists.

if you want to use CurrentSpeed for example
local playerData = ClientGlobals.PlayerData

function controller.init()
    -- to get it:
    local speed = playerData.Data.CurrentSpeed

    -- to observe it:
    playerData:Observe({"CurrentSpeed"}, function(speed: number?)
        print(speed)
    end)
end


note that values can be nil if they are observed without calling WaitForLoaded first, which yields until the first initial batch of player data arrives. on startup the data could be nil. my recommended pattern in most cases is

local playerData = ClientGlobals.PlayerData

function controller.init()
    playerData:Observe({"CurrentSpeed"}, function(speed: number?)
        if not speed then return end

        -- speed has loaded
        print(speed)
    end)
end

