# Service / Controllers
when you make a service/controller 99% of the time you should be using  . instead of : like the rest of the codebase, and as a general rule of thumb anything short of an object should be using .

use camelCase for functions, only exception is for object methods i.e object:Method(), and everything else singleton.method() 

# Trove (Lifecycle Management)
Use Trove (`ReplicatedStorage.Packages.Trove`) when you have multiple things to clean up (connections, instances, signals, etc.) to prevent memory leaks. Don't overuse it for singular objects - use judgement.

```luau
local Trove = require(ReplicatedStorage.Packages.Trove)

local trove = Trove.new()
trove:Connect(workspace.ChildAdded, handler)
trove:Add(somePart)
trove:Add(someOtherPart)

-- do work...

trove:Destroy() -- cleans everything at once
```

**Typing:** Use `typeof(Trove.new())` for function parameters (the exported `Trove.Trove` type causes false linter errors due to complex recursive types):
```luau
local function doSomething(trove: typeof(Trove.new()))
    trove:Add(instance)
end
```

Key methods: `Add(obj)`, `Clone(instance)`, `Connect(signal, fn)`, `Construct(Class)`, `Extend()` for sub-troves, `Remove(obj)` destroys, `Pop(obj)` removes without destroying, `Clean()` cleans without destroying the trove, `WrapClean()` returns a cleanup function.

# Events
events have an "expiration" timer that can be found in ClientGlobals.ActiveEvents (replicator) or ServerGlobals.ActiveEvents (table)

events on both the server and client have a run function that returns a cleanup function to end that event.
if an event is ran again, the duration will be extended and the function wont rerun. if this is too limiting lmk and i can adjust it.

events should, for the most part, be self contained and instead adjust global reusable values. for example if we wanted to add a 10% chance of a specific type of wave while the event is active, instead of manually doing that we would edit the wave module to have a :RegisterEventWave(waveType, weight) function and deregister it when event ends

script templates are in EventController and EventService, both are structured mostly the same

use F2 > runevent eventname to test an event 

# Admin Commands
we're using conch. new commands go in `ServerScriptService/Server/Services/AdminService/Commands/`. if you need more types edit conchTypes. theres a command template

# Configurations / Stats
anything config related that needs to be used across multiple scripts (for example, rarities and their associated data) should be added to the Config ModuleScript in shared.

explicitly return these configurations as return t :: typeof(t) & { [string]: typeHere }

Rarities for reference: 
--!strict
