return Rarities :: typeof(Rarities) & { [string]: Rarity }

# Binding Robux purchase buttons to products / gamepasses
Tag it with ProductButton
Set either a ProductName or GamepassName attribute, this should be a key in Pay2Win.ProductIds or GamepassIds
Create a TextLabel called PriceLabel inside the button (optional)

everything else is handled automatically 

# Popups / Notifications
Use the Popup module to display notifications and popups. In most cases this should just be Popup.Info, but If you need something more specific then feel free to extend the module. 
UIModule has been stripped of all its notification functions, you have to use this now

# Gamepasses
Owned gamepasses are located in Profile.Data.Gamepasses and the Replicator equivalent

# Lighting
all changes to Lighting including blurs should go through LightingController & GameValues.ActiveLighting, which uses priorities to know which lighting to use. if your confused on how to do something (probably transitions) ping me. we need to keep this all centralised and reusable to prevent a giant mess later
^ this means you should almost never use game:GetService("Lighting") directly
theres also a script you can use to copy the entire lighting properties and children as a folder, that you should place in Assets.Lighting 

# PromptProductPurchases
all PromptProductPurchases should be replaced with this new event or use the PurchaseButton component, which handles this automatically including gifting. take a look at the GiftButton in the VIP frame in the shop to see how thats done

if you have to insist use:
local PromptProductEvent = Net:RemoteEvent("PromptProduct")
PromptProductEvent:FireServer(productId, giftPlayer)

